\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\i\f1\fs32 1. What word would best describe how an intrusion detection system operates? [IDS]\b0\i0\par
Intrusion Detection Systems (IDSs) operates in a \ul proactive \ulnone manner. Unlike for example controls like firewalls, authentication and access control, that are preventive, an IDS complements with type of sensor that monitors and activity to identify malicious and suspicious events. It can be compared with a smoke detector which raises an alarm at specific occations. All IDSs has a response function which for example could alert a human who can decide what further actions that are needed. However, sometimes, an IDS goes into protection mode to isolate a suspected intruder and constrain access. Such a system is called an Intrusion Prevention System (IPS). So the IDS is a subset of the IPS.  \par

