\b 25. In the context of software security, such as OS security, eight design principles were formulated more than 40 years ago. Despite the relative age, they remain valid even today. Describe any four of these design principles. [OS Security]\par
\par
\b0 Good design principles are good for security. Here follow a list that is essential in building a secure, solid and trusted operating system: \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Enforcing of Least Privalege\ulnone\par

\pard A policy that determines that a user should have as few privalege as possible (only to the projects that they are part of). \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Economy of Design\ulnone\par

\pard A simple design will lead to simplcity in analysis and therefore much less flaws introduced. \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Open Design\ulnone\par

\pard Design should be open, established and tested. No system should depend on holding certain information secret. \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Complete Mediation\ulnone\par

\pard Check and recheck all accesses everytime. \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Permission Based\ulnone\par

\pard The default state for a user should be not to have access to any object at all. \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Separation of Privalege\ulnone\par

\pard The essential part of the OS may have higher privalege, but user programs should have a significantly lower privalege. \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Least Common Mechanism\ulnone\par

\pard Mechanisms used to access resources should not be shared. \par
\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\ul Ease of Use\ulnone\par

\pard Information security and security controls should not make it harder to use a function. \b\i\par

